1 how pizza works
The “Pizza” program is a simple Python script that calculates the total price of a pizza order based on the provided rules. 
It collects information about the order, applies appropriate discounts based on whether it’s Tuesday, whether delivery is required, and whether the customer used the BPP app. 
The program uses functions to avoid code duplication and ensures meaningful identifiers for variables and constants.
